Sentencas: In present paper, La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF)/Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (GDC)/LSCF structure has been studied to understand electrode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Electrochemical behavior of LSCF/GDC interface in symmetric cell: An application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The nanocrystalline powder required for screen printing was obtained through solution combustion synthesis with glycine as a fuel.
Titulo: Electrochemical behavior of LSCF/GDC interface in symmetric cell: An application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The LSCF powder synthesized at fuel to oxidant ratio of two is calcined at 900 degrees C as TG-DTA reveals thermal stability only beyond 900 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical behavior of LSCF/GDC interface in symmetric cell: An application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The X-ray diffraction pattern of calcined powder demonstrates rhombohedral perovskite structured LSCF with 27 nm crystallite size.
Titulo: Electrochemical behavior of LSCF/GDC interface in symmetric cell: An application in solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: However, dynamic laser scattering shows 0.9 mu m sized agglomerates while TEM shows 74 nm particles.

Sentencas: For potential application in solid oxide fuel cells, the temperature programmed reduction and oxidation were done on the LSCF.

Sentencas: The results exhibit strong reduction and oxidation behavior around 860 and 388 degrees C, respectively.
